<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/22292408-barbara-ruth">Barbara Ruth</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I also tracked down the book after having loved the movie. I may love them equally. Yes, the book is slightly different, and more detailed in that you<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I also tracked down the book after having loved the movie. I may love them equally. Yes, the book is slightly different, and more detailed in that you get deeper into the heads of the characters and some of the motivations that aren't quite as clear from watching the film become clearer when you read the background (why the neighbors are willing to take one child but not the other for instance). I can't recommend the book enough.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
