</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/22292408-barbara-ruth"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1374084399i/22292408._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/22292408-barbara-ruth">Barbara Ruth</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    The bond money is refunded because she proved to the sheriff that her father was dead (bringing him her father's hands) and not that he had skipped ou<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The bond money is refunded because she proved to the sheriff that her father was dead (bringing him her father's hands) and not that he had skipped out on his bond. The bond money that had been paid was paid to get her father out of jail so that he could be killed before he testified, but the bondsman didn't actually know who gave him the money, so he gave it to Ree.<br />It's pretty clearly implied that one of the extended family members killed her father. That's why the family was able to take her to find his body. Her uncle figures out who the killer is when the bondsman says something about the man he interacted with looking like he wasn't even awake. One of the characters is known as "Sleepy John", and that's a clue that he was the killer.<br /><a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
